1
00:00:04,768 --> 00:00:08,798
I knew by the time 
I was 14 or 15,
 

2
00:00:08,798 --> 00:00:14,518
that it was all lies,
it was all nonsense.

3
00:00:15,078 --> 00:00:17,305
Plastic people …
[Laughing]

4
00:00:17,535 --> 00:00:21,022
[Plastic People | Knowledge above Mortality]

5
00:00:21,502 --> 00:00:23,940
All superficial.

6
00:00:24,730 --> 00:00:27,660
“The boast of heraldry, 
the pomp of pow’r,

7
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:30,680
And all that beauty,
all that wealth e’er gave,

8
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,310
Awaits alike th’ inevitable hour.
 

9
00:00:32,310 --> 00:00:35,737
The paths of glory 
lead but to the grave.”

10
00:00:40,838 --> 00:00:43,688
Or as Frank Zappa said,

11
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:47,130
“You can have it, 
I don’t need it,

12
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:49,830
Take your TV tube 
and eat it.”

13
00:00:52,255 --> 00:00:54,335
It’s all the same:

14
00:00:54,842 --> 00:00:57,822
you wake up one day 
and figure out—

15
00:00:57,822 --> 00:01:05,452
you are being inundated
with humanistic sloganeering

16
00:01:05,452 --> 00:01:09,855
being stuffed down your soul,
 

17
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:14,169
telling you to believe that, 
 

18
00:01:14,169 --> 00:01:16,579
“We’ve moved away
from the monarch conception.

19
00:01:16,579 --> 00:01:19,299
Now you’re king!”

20
00:01:20,088 --> 00:01:23,565
—Yeah … 
What kind of king you are?

21
00:01:23,565 --> 00:01:27,503
“Now you are the king, 
you are the queen.”

22
00:01:28,962 --> 00:01:32,602
People who swallow 
humanistic sloganeering—

23
00:01:32,602 --> 00:01:34,572
hook, line, and sinker—

24
00:01:34,572 --> 00:01:41,173
are ill-prepared to deal 
with mortal existence,

25
00:01:42,975 --> 00:01:47,655
which is the only type 
available here presently.

26
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:56,497
“The paths of glory lead 
but to the grave.”

27
00:01:56,497 --> 00:01:58,937
It all ends up in the graveyard, 
then what?

28
00:01:58,937 --> 00:02:00,283
—Oh, nobody knows.

29
00:02:00,283 --> 00:02:01,503
—No, you don’t know,

30
00:02:01,503 --> 00:02:03,253
and nobody you know, knows.

31
00:02:03,253 --> 00:02:06,203
But that doesn’t mean 
that nobody knows.

32
00:02:10,822 --> 00:02:13,882
Knowledge above mortality—

33
00:02:13,882 --> 00:02:16,312
āmnāyaḥ prāha tattvaṁ

34
00:02:16,312 --> 00:02:19,822
If the Infinite can make Itself 
known to the finite,

35
00:02:19,822 --> 00:02:22,273
if you can accept 
that prospect

36
00:02:22,273 --> 00:02:25,033
that by in a realm 
of infinite possibility

37
00:02:25,043 --> 00:02:28,003
the Infinite can make Itself 
known to the finite,

38
00:02:28,013 --> 00:02:30,153
then you put yourself 
in a position

39
00:02:30,153 --> 00:02:34,153
to appreciate the value 
of revealed truth.

40
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:39,140
This is theism, 
basic theism 101.

41
00:02:41,157 --> 00:02:43,397
Then we can proceed 
from there.

